data.title: Robert B
data.content:
Becoming a part of history at #statelibrarynsw sharing my portrait. Taken on a sojourn to #galway 
Stopped into a fish and chip shop by the name of #hookedgalway “You need to come face-to-face with the past, not as some naive, easily wounded boy, but as a grown-up, independent professional. Not to see what you want to see, but what you must see. Otherwise you’ll carry around that baggage for the rest of your life.”
Haruki Murakami.

Those who smile will encourage others to do the same. 
Here’s to making history and being apart of it face-to-face.
